      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SUNLIT AMBER (4) doesn't win out of turn but looks close to breaking through. Has finished in the placings two on end now, the latest when third (22.24) at this track. Solid record at the distance winning three races. Has never been out of the placings from two starts out of this box. One of the leading chances. MYSTIC ART (1) turned in a modest effort most recently when seventh at Capalaba over 366m behind Zipping Tesfay (20.81) in a Grade 5. Was in the money prior to that. The form from her last run is stacking up nicely. Key player if finds best. SWIFT CANNON (7) showed strong early pace and stuck on well despite finishing out of the placings when fourth over 352m this track in 20.16. Has the ability to give this a shake. TUKI BEACH (8) should be thereabouts despite an unplaced run here most recently.",
